8:
I don't even have to say anything,
and food just... APPEARS! There's
always someone to hang out with!
And I can go home whenever I want!
12:
This is the BEST vacation spot ever!
This is LITERALLY what I imagined
living in another world would be like!
18:
No! It's AMAZING! I just feel like it's
spoiling me...
21: Hey, Stella, I've got a question.
24:
Is there anywhere I can go to let off
some steam and earn some cash?
35:
This is for the training I skipped the
day before that!
39:
And... This is for the delicious dinner
I'm gonna have tonight!
43:
You, uh... counting calories or
something?
47:
No way. I've just been a bit too
spoiled by you guys lately. This is my
way of dealing with that.
50:
If I don't, I'm gonna eat and drink
myself outta house and home when
I go back!
54:
Seriously, don't underestimate my
lack of self-control.
59:
You almost sound like you're proud
of that.
62:
Didn't you come here to relax
though? You're putting in a lot of
hours for someone on vacation.
66:
I AM relaxing. When am I gonna get
another chance to explore a
randomly generated dungeon like
this?
77:
Come on, this isn't some virtual
reality—
85:
Hey, you all right? You hurt
anywhere?
91:
Okay, okay, calm down. We'll get you
out of here.
96: Nimbus, take the kid! I'll make a path!
106:
So you wanted to show off to your
friends, is that it?
109:
They're always telling me I could
never be an adventurer like them.
111:
Sure, they can use magic and junk,
but that doesn't give them the right
to tell me what I can and can't do!
120: No... I wouldn't have any right to.
124:
It's just... People die. You know that,
don't you? And it happens a lot
easier than you think.
127:
But it's easier to not think about that.
I mean... There isn't anything you
can do about it, so why worry, right?
132:
Yep. But that just makes you even
cooler in my book. Even without any
powers, you're giving it your all,
aren't yah?
134:
That's why you need to figure out
what you CAN do. Maybe learn to
use a weapon or something. That
way you can keep yourself safe AND
prove the haters wrong.
137: Do you really think I can do it?
143:
And anyone who tells you hard work
is for nerds is just jealous! So feel
free to throw a few harsh words their
way when that happens!
148:
So all I gotta do is say this spell, and
I'll perform magic? This looks like
something out of those sketchy
occult sites...
151:
Let's see... First, you call on the
elements, then define said element,
and give a command... Got it.
155:
O waters of life! The elixir that
nourishes my brethren! I beckon you
to my hand!
170:
You're not thinking of holding that
brat's hand until he makes
something of himself, are you?
173:
Of course not... But I do want to help
if I can.
176:
I get that I'm just doing this to make
myself feel better, and I'm not
gonna make a HUGE difference.
178:
But I mean, if it worked for me,
maybe that little push will work for
that kid too.
182: What if he doesn't want your help?
187:
That's just part of being a
hero—helping out no matter who
pushes back, even if you get a
punch in the face as thanks.
191:
Ha, that attitude of yours is gonna
cost you one day.
194:
Anyway, if there's something you
can't do, just leave it to someone
who can. You've got buttloads of
allies here now.
198:
Sounds like you can't leave well
enough alone either.
202:
Shut it. Now come on, let's see who's
in the kitchen.
